# Step 5

Now we'll use our new css in the html

Start by linking the css files, add it in the `<!-- build:css -->` section.
This will be part of the build process later on.

__`index.html`__
```
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/app.css"/>
```

Now we'll add some classes to apply our styles

> ### En massa klasser som ska läggas till, vet inte hur mycket detalj vi ska gå in på här
> ### Kanske att vi lägger till css-koden här på något sätt

Start by adding the class `l-flexbox`, this will set `display:flex` on the elements

__`index.html`__

```html
<body>
<div class="l-flexbox" ng-controller="appController">
   <!--Header-->
   <header>
      Live now ({{liveEvents.length}})
   </header>
   <!--Main-->
   <main class="l-flexbox">
      <div class="l-flexbox" ng-repeat="liveEvent in liveEvents | limitTo : 3">
         <!--Competitors and path-->
         <div class="l-flexbox">
            <!--Competitors-->
            <div class="l-flexbox">
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span>{{liveEvent.event.homeName}}</span>
               </div>
               <div>-</div>
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span>{{liveEvent.event.awayName}}</span>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
   </main>
</div>
</body>
```

Next we'll add some classes to define how things should flex

- l-vertical: sets the flex orientation to vertical

- l-expander: makes the element take up 100% width and height

- l-flexed: sets the flex value to 1 on the element

- l-pack-start: aligns the child elements to the beginning of it's orientation.

- l-pack-center: aligns the elements to the center of it's orientation

- l-flex-3: Sets the flex value to 3

```html
<body>
<div class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-expander" ng-controller="appController">
   <!--Header-->
   <header>
      Live now ({{liveEvents.length}})
   </header>
   <!--Main-->
   <main class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-flexed l-pack-start">
      <div class="l-flexbox l-vertical"
           ng-repeat="liveEvent in liveEvents | limitTo : 3">

         <!--Competitors and path-->
         <div class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-pack-center l-flex-3">
            <!--Competitors-->
            <div class="l-flexbox">
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span>{{liveEvent.event.homeName}}</span>
               </div>
               <div>-</div>
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span>{{liveEvent.event.awayName}}</span>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
   </main>
</div>
</body>
```

We can add some classes to add padding to our elements
The following classes will add 15 pixels padding to the top, right, bottom and left respectively
- l-pt-15
- l-pr-15
- l-pb-15
- l-pl-15

Following the same pattern the following classes will add 5 pixels of padding to the left and to the right.
- l-pl-5
- l-pr-5

To make sure that our team names only display as one line we can add a class `text-truncate` to truncate them using ellipsis.

```html
<body>
<div class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-expander" ng-controller="appController">
   <!--Header-->
   <header class="l-pl-15">
      Live now ({{liveEvents.length}})
   </header>
   <!--Main-->
   <main class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-flexed l-pack-start">
      <div class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-pb-15 l-pt-15 l-pl-15 l-pr-15"
           ng-repeat="liveEvent in liveEvents | limitTo : 3">

         <!--Competitors and path-->
         <div class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-pack-center l-flex-3">
            <!--Competitors-->
            <div class="l-flexbox">
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span class="text-truncate">{{liveEvent.event.homeName}}</span>
               </div>
               <div class="l-pl-5 l-pr-5">-</div>
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span class="text-truncate">{{liveEvent.event.awayName}}</span>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
   </main>
</div>
</body>
```

The final step in the styling is to add some of our classes containing the colors that we specified in the `_variables.css` file

- kw-body : body element
- kw-card : the first child of the body
- kw-header : the header element
- kw-event: the element containing the event
- kw-event-name-container: the container of our team name elements
- kw-event-name: the team name element
- kw-event-name-divider: the hyphen element

```html
<body class="kw-body">
<div class="kw-card l-flexbox l-vertical l-expander" ng-controller="appController">
   <!--Header-->
   <header class="kw-header l-pl-15">
      Live now ({{liveEvents.length}})
   </header>
   <!--Main-->
   <main class="l-flexbox l-vertical l-flexed l-pack-start">
      <div class="kw-event l-flexbox l-vertical l-pb-15 l-pt-15 l-pl-15 l-pr-15"
           ng-repeat="liveEvent in liveEvents | limitTo : 3">

         <!--Competitors and path-->
         <div class="kw-event-name-container l-flexbox l-vertical l-pack-center l-flex-3">
            <!--Competitors-->
            <div class="kw-event-name l-flexbox">
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span class="text-truncate">{{liveEvent.event.homeName}}</span>
               </div>
               <div class="kw-event-name-divider l-pl-5 l-pr-5">-</div>
               <div class="l-flexbox">
                  <span class="text-truncate">{{liveEvent.event.awayName}}</span>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
   </main>
</div>
</body>
```

You should now have some styling applied to your event list.

The last event probably looks a bit chopped off, we'll fix that in the next step.
